Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Unicode Processing and Analysis Framework

Production-grade Unicode processing system designed to surpass competitors like
Python's unicodedata, ICU library, Node.js Intl, and Java's Character class.
Comprehensive Unicode handling with full normalization, classification, and analysis.

Key Features:
- Complete Unicode 15.0+ support with all character categories
- Unicode normalization (NFC, NFD, NFKC, NFKD) with composition/decomposition
- Advanced character classification and property analysis
- Bidirectional text processing with proper RTL/LTR handling
- Case conversion with locale-aware transformations
- Unicode-aware string comparison and collation
- Grapheme cluster and word boundary detection
- Script detection and language identification
- Emoji classification and variation sequence handling
- Unicode security analysis with confusable character detection
- Performance-optimized algorithms for large text processing
- Full Unicode database integration with property lookups

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized Unicode
algorithms and comprehensive character database. Provides both
high-level Unicode processing APIs and low-level character manipulation
utilities for maximum flexibility and performance.
:End Note

Import "collections" as Collections
Import "string/format" as Format

Note: Core Unicode Types and Structures
Type called "UnicodeCharacter":
