Note: Unicode Character Analysis and Classification
Process called "get_unicode_character" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeCharacter:
    Note: Get complete Unicode character information
    Let char_info be lookup_character_info with codepoint as codepoint
    Let category be classify_character_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Let bidi_type be determine_bidirectional_type with codepoint as codepoint
    Let script be detect_character_script with codepoint as codepoint
    Let block be find_unicode_block with codepoint as codepoint
    Let case_mapping be generate_case_mapping with codepoint as codepoint
    Let properties be extract_character_properties with codepoint as codepoint Return UnicodeCharacter with:
    codepoint as codepoint
    utf8_sequence as codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as codepoint
    utf16_sequence as codepoint_to_utf16 with codepoint as codepoint
    utf32_value as codepoint
    character_name as char_info.name
    category as category
    combining_class as char_info.combining_class
    bidirectional_type as bidi_type
    numeric_value as char_info.numeric_value
    case_mapping as case_mapping
    script as script
    block as block
    properties as properties
    metadata as dictionary containing "analyzed_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "classify_character_category" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeCategory:
    Note: Classify character into Unicode general category
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 65 and codepoint is less than or equal to 90:
    Return LetterUppercase
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 97 and codepoint is less than or equal to 122:
    Return LetterLowercase
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 48 and codepoint is less than or equal to 57:
    Return NumberDecimalDigit
    Otherwise if codepoint is equal to 32:
    Return SeparatorSpace
    Otherwise if codepoint is equal to 9 or codepoint is equal to 10 or codepoint is equal to 13:
    Return OtherControl
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 192 and codepoint is less than or equal to 214:
    Return LetterUppercase
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 224 and codepoint is less than or equal to 246:
    Return LetterLowercase
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 8192 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8303:
    Return SeparatorSpace
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 8448 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8527:
    Return SymbolMath
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 65536:
    Return determine_high_codepoint_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Otherwise:
    Return OtherNotAssigned

Process called "determine_high_codepoint_category" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeCategory:
    Note: Classify high codepoint characters (supplementary planes)
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 127744 and codepoint is less than or equal to 128511:
    Note: Emoji blocks
    Return SymbolOther
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 131072 and codepoint is less than or equal to 173791:
    Note: CJK Extension B
    Return LetterOther
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 173824 and codepoint is less than or equal to 177983:
    Note: CJK Extension C
    Return LetterOther
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 177984 and codepoint is less than or equal to 178207:
    Note: CJK Extension D
    Return LetterOther
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 194560 and codepoint is less than or equal to 195103:
    Note: CJK Extension F
    Return LetterOther
    Otherwise:
    Return OtherNotAssigned

Process called "detect_character_script" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeScript:
    Note: Detect Unicode script for character
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 65 and codepoint is less than or equal to 122:
    Return Latin
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 880 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1023:
    Return Greek
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1024 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1327:
    Return Cyrillic
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1329 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1423:
    Return Armenian
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1424 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1535:
    Return Hebrew
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1536 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1791:
    Return Arabic
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 2304 and codepoint is less than or equal to 2431:
    Return Devanagari
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 2432 and codepoint is less than or equal to 2559:
    Return Bengali
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 2688 and codepoint is less than or equal to 2815:
    Return Tamil
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 3585 and codepoint is less than or equal to 3711:
    Return Thai
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 4352 and codepoint is less than or equal to 4607:
    Return Hangul
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 12352 and codepoint is less than or equal to 12447:
    Return Hiragana
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 12448 and codepoint is less than or equal to 12543:
    Return Katakana
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 19968 and codepoint is less than or equal to 40959:
    Return Han
    Otherwise:
    Return Common

Process called "determine_bidirectional_type" that takes codepoint as Integer returns BidirectionalType:
    Note: Determine bidirectional character type for text layout
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 65 and codepoint is less than or equal to 122:
    Return LeftToRight
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 48 and codepoint is less than or equal to 57:
    Return EuropeanNumber
    Otherwise if codepoint is equal to 32 or codepoint is equal to 9:
    Return Whitespace
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1536 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1791:
    Return ArabicLetter
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1424 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1535:
    Return RightToLeft
    Otherwise if codepoint is equal to 10 or codepoint is equal to 13:
    Return ParagraphSeparator
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 8234 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8238:
    Return determine_directional_override with codepoint as codepoint
    Otherwise:
    Return OtherNeutral

Process called "determine_directional_override" that takes codepoint as Integer returns BidirectionalType:
    Note: Determine specific directional override types
    Match codepoint:
    When 8234:
    Return LeftToRightEmbedding
    When 8235:
    Return RightToLeftEmbedding
    When 8236:
    Return PopDirectionalFormat
    When 8237:
    Return LeftToRightOverride
    When 8238:
    Return RightToLeftOverride
    Otherwise:
    Return OtherNeutral

Process called "extract_character_properties" that takes codepoint as Integer returns List[UnicodeProperty]:
    Note: Extract all Unicode properties for character
    Let properties be list containing If is_alphabetic with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Alphabetic to properties
    If is_numeric with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Numeric to properties
    If is_decimal with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Decimal to properties
    If is_digit with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Digit to properties
    If is_whitespace with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Whitespace to properties
    If is_control with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Control to properties
    If is_uppercase with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Uppercase to properties
    If is_lowercase with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Lowercase to properties
    If is_titlecase with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Titlecase to properties
    If is_cased_letter with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add CasedLetter to properties
    If is_math with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Math to properties
    If is_emoji with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add Emoji to properties
    If is_emoji_presentation with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add EmojiPresentation to properties
    If is_grapheme_extend with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add GraphemeExtend to properties
    If is_grapheme_base with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add GraphemeBase to properties
    If is_id_start with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add IDStart to properties
    If is_id_continue with codepoint as codepoint:
    Add IDContinue to properties Return properties

Note: Unicode Property Testing Functions
Process called "is_alphabetic" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Alphabetic property
    Let category be classify_character_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Match category:
    When LetterUppercase:
    Return true
    When LetterLowercase:
    Return true
    When LetterTitlecase:
    Return true
    When LetterModifier:
    Return true
    When LetterOther:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_numeric" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Numeric property
    Let category be classify_character_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Match category:
    When NumberDecimalDigit:
    Return true
    When NumberLetter:
    Return true
    When NumberOther:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return has_numeric_value with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "is_decimal" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character represents decimal digit
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 48 and codepoint is less than or equal to 57

Process called "is_digit" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character represents any digit (including super/subscript)
    If is_decimal with codepoint as codepoint:
    Return true
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 8304 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8313:
    Note: Superscript digits
    Return true
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 8320 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8329:
    Note: Subscript digits
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_whitespace" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has White_Space property
    Match codepoint:
    When 9: Note: Tab
    Return true
    When 10: Note: Line Feed
    Return true
    When 11: Note: Vertical Tab
    Return true
    When 12: Note: Form Feed
    Return true
    When 13: Note: Carriage Return
    Return true
    When 32: Note: Space
    Return true
    When 133: Note: Next Line
    Return true
    When 160: Note: No-Break Space
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 8192 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8202 Note: Various spaces

Process called "is_control" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character is control character
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 0 and codepoint is less than or equal to 31 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 127 and codepoint is less than or equal to 159

Process called "is_uppercase" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Uppercase property
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 65 and codepoint is less than or equal to 90 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 192 and codepoint is less than or equal to 214 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 216 and codepoint is less than or equal to 222

Process called "is_lowercase" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Lowercase property
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 97 and codepoint is less than or equal to 122 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 224 and codepoint is less than or equal to 246 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 248 and codepoint is less than or equal to 255

Process called "is_titlecase" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Titlecase property
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 453 and codepoint is less than or equal to 459 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 498 and codepoint is less than or equal to 501

Process called "is_cased_letter" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character is a cased letter
    Return is_uppercase with codepoint as codepoint or is_lowercase with codepoint as codepoint or is_titlecase with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "is_math" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Math property
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 43 and codepoint is less than or equal to 43 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 60 and codepoint is less than or equal to 62 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 8704 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8959

Process called "is_emoji" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has Emoji property
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 127744 and codepoint is less than or equal to 128511 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 128512 and codepoint is less than or equal to 128591 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 9728 and codepoint is less than or equal to 9983

Process called "is_emoji_presentation" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character has default emoji presentation
    Return is_emoji with codepoint as codepoint and not has_text_presentation with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "is_grapheme_extend" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character extends grapheme clusters
    Let category be classify_character_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Match category:
    When MarkNonspacing:
    Return true
    When MarkEnclosing:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_grapheme_base" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character can be base of grapheme cluster
    Return not is_grapheme_extend with codepoint as codepoint and not is_control with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "is_id_start" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character can start identifier
    If is_alphabetic with codepoint as codepoint:
    Return true
    Otherwise if codepoint is equal to 95: Note: Underscore
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_id_continue" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if character can continue identifier
    Return is_id_start with codepoint as codepoint or is_decimal with codepoint as codepoint or is_grapheme_extend with codepoint as codepoint

Note: Unicode Normalization and Text Processing
Process called "normalize_unicode" that takes text as String and form as NormalizationForm returns NormalizationResult:
    Note: Normalize Unicode text using specified form
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let normalized_text be ""
    Match form:
    When NFC:
    Set normalized_text to normalize_to_nfc with text as text
    When NFD:
    Set normalized_text to normalize_to_nfd with text as text
    When NFKC:
    Set normalized_text to normalize_to_nfkc with text as text
    When NFKD:
    Set normalized_text to normalize_to_nfkd with text as text Let combining_classes be extract_combining_classes with text as normalized_text Return NormalizationResult with:
    normalized_text as normalized_text
    form_used as form
    composition_applied as form is equal to NFC or form is equal to NFKC
    decomposition_applied as form is equal to NFD or form is equal to NFKD
    canonical_combining_classes as combining_classes
    metadata as dictionary containing "normalization_time" as get_current_timestamp - start_time

Process called "normalize_to_nfd" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize to NFD (Canonical Decomposition)
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let decomposed be canonical_decomposition with codepoint as codepoint
    If length of decomposed is greater than 1:
    For each decomp_point in decomposed:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as decomp_point
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as codepoint Return reorder_combining_marks with text as result

Process called "normalize_to_nfc" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize to NFC (Canonical Decomposition + Composition)
    Let decomposed be normalize_to_nfd with text as text
    Return canonical_composition with text as decomposed

Process called "normalize_to_nfkd" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize to NFKD (Compatibility Decomposition)
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let decomposed be compatibility_decomposition with codepoint as codepoint
    If length of decomposed is greater than 1:
    For each decomp_point in decomposed:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as decomp_point
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as codepoint Return reorder_combining_marks with text as result

Process called "normalize_to_nfkc" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize to NFKC (Compatibility Decomposition + Composition)
    Let decomposed be normalize_to_nfkd with text as text
    Return canonical_composition with text as decomposed

Process called "canonical_decomposition" that takes codepoint as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Get canonical decomposition of character
    Note: This would normally use Unicode database, simplified here
    Match codepoint:
    When 192: Note: À
    Return list containing 65, 768
    When 193: Note: Á
    Return list containing 65, 769
    When 224: Note: à
    Return list containing 97, 768
    When 225: Note: á
    Return list containing 97, 769
    Otherwise:
    Return list containing codepoint

Process called "compatibility_decomposition" that takes codepoint as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Get compatibility decomposition of character
    Match codepoint:
    When 8486: Note: Ω (Ohm sign)
    Return list containing 937
    When 65313: Note: Ａ (fullwidth A)
    Return list containing 65
    When 65345: Note: ａ (fullwidth a)
    Return list containing 97
    Otherwise:
    Return canonical_decomposition with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "canonical_composition" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Apply canonical composition to decomposed text
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text
    Let result_codepoints be list containing
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of codepoints:
    Let current be codepoints[i] If i + 1 is less than length of codepoints:
    Let next be codepoints[i + 1]
    Let composed be try_compose with base as current and combining as next If composed is not equal to 0:
    Add composed to result_codepoints
    Set i to i + 2
    Otherwise:
    Add current to result_codepoints
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise:
    Add current to result_codepoints
    Set i to i + 1 Return codepoints_to_string with codepoints as result_codepoints

Process called "try_compose" that takes base as Integer and combining as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Try to compose base + combining character
    If base is equal to 65 and combining is equal to 768: Note: A + grave
    Return 192 Note: À
    Otherwise if base is equal to 65 and combining is equal to 769: Note: A + acute
    Return 193 Note: Á
    Otherwise if base is equal to 97 and combining is equal to 768: Note: a + grave
    Return 224 Note: à
    Otherwise if base is equal to 97 and combining is equal to 769: Note: a + acute
    Return 225 Note: á
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "reorder_combining_marks" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Reorder combining marks by combining class
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text
    Let result be list containing
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of codepoints:
    Let current be codepoints[i]
    Add current to result If is_base_character with codepoint as current:
    Note: Collect combining marks
    Let combining_marks be list containing
    Set i to i + 1 While i is less than length of codepoints and is_combining_mark with codepoint as codepoints[i]:
    Add codepoints[i] to combining_marks
    Set i to i + 1 Note: Sort combining marks by combining class
    Let sorted_marks be sort_combining_marks with marks as combining_marks
    For each mark in sorted_marks:
    Add mark to result
    Otherwise:
    Set i to i + 1 Return codepoints_to_string with codepoints as result

Note: Case Conversion and Mapping
Process called "generate_case_mapping" that takes codepoint as Integer returns CaseMapping:
    Note: Generate comprehensive case mapping for character
    Let lowercase be to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Let uppercase be to_uppercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Let titlecase be to_titlecase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Let foldcase be to_foldcase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint Return CaseMapping with:
    lowercase as codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as lowercase
    uppercase as codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as uppercase
    titlecase as codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as titlecase
    foldcase as codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as foldcase
    has_special_casing as lowercase is not equal to codepoint or uppercase is not equal to codepoint
    locale_specific as has_locale_specific_casing with codepoint as codepoint
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "unicode_lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Convert text to lowercase with full Unicode support
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let lowercase_point be to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as lowercase_point Return result

Process called "unicode_uppercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Convert text to uppercase with full Unicode support
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let uppercase_point be to_uppercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as uppercase_point Return result

Process called "unicode_titlecase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Convert text to titlecase with proper word boundaries
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text
    Let at_word_start be true For each codepoint in codepoints:
    If at_word_start and is_cased_letter with codepoint as codepoint:
    Let titlecase_point be to_titlecase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as titlecase_point
    Set at_word_start to false
    Otherwise if is_word_boundary with codepoint as codepoint:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as codepoint
    Set at_word_start to true
    Otherwise:
    Let lowercase_point be to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as lowercase_point Return result

Process called "unicode_casefold" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Apply case folding for caseless comparison
    Let result be ""
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let folded_point be to_foldcase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as folded_point Return result

Process called "to_lowercase_codepoint" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Convert single codepoint to lowercase
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 65 and codepoint is less than or equal to 90:
    Return codepoint + 32
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 192 and codepoint is less than or equal to 214:
    Return codepoint + 32
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 216 and codepoint is less than or equal to 222:
    Return codepoint + 32
    Otherwise:
    Return codepoint

Process called "to_uppercase_codepoint" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Convert single codepoint to uppercase
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 97 and codepoint is less than or equal to 122:
    Return codepoint - 32
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 224 and codepoint is less than or equal to 246:
    Return codepoint - 32
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 248 and codepoint is less than or equal to 254:
    Return codepoint - 32
    Otherwise:
    Return codepoint

Process called "to_titlecase_codepoint" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Convert single codepoint to titlecase (usually same as uppercase)
    Return to_uppercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "to_foldcase_codepoint" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Apply case folding to single codepoint
    Let uppercase_point be to_uppercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint
    Return to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as uppercase_point

Note: Grapheme Cluster and Text Segmentation
Process called "split_into_grapheme_clusters" that takes text as String returns List[GraphemeCluster]:
    Note: Split text into grapheme clusters (user-perceived characters)
    Let clusters be list containing
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text
    Let current_cluster_start be 0
    Let current_cluster_codepoints be list containing
    Let position be 0 For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Add codepoint to current_cluster_codepoints If is_grapheme_boundary_after with codepoints as codepoints and position as position:
    Let cluster_text be codepoints_to_string with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    Let cluster_type be determine_grapheme_cluster_type with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    Let properties be extract_cluster_properties with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints Let cluster be GraphemeCluster with:
    text as cluster_text
    codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    start_position as current_cluster_start
    end_position as position + 1
    cluster_type as cluster_type
    properties as properties
    metadata as dictionary containing Add cluster to clusters Set current_cluster_start to position + 1
    Set current_cluster_codepoints to list containing Set position to position + 1 Note: Handle final cluster
    If length of current_cluster_codepoints is greater than 0:
    Let cluster_text be codepoints_to_string with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    Let cluster_type be determine_grapheme_cluster_type with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    Let properties be extract_cluster_properties with codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints Let cluster be GraphemeCluster with:
    text as cluster_text
    codepoints as current_cluster_codepoints
    start_position as current_cluster_start
    end_position as position
    cluster_type as cluster_type
    properties as properties
    metadata as dictionary containing Add cluster to clusters Return clusters

Process called "is_grapheme_boundary_after" that takes codepoints as List[Integer] and position as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if there's a grapheme boundary after position
    If position is greater than or equal to length of codepoints - 1:
    Return true Let current be codepoints[position]
    Let next be codepoints[position + 1] Note: Never break between CR and LF
    If current is equal to 13 and next is equal to 10:
    Return false Note: Break after controls
    If is_control with codepoint as current or current is equal to 13 or current is equal to 10:
    Return true Note: Don't break before extending characters
    If is_grapheme_extend with codepoint as next:
    Return false Note: Don't break within emoji sequences
    If is_emoji with codepoint as current and next is equal to 65039: Note: Variation Selector-16
    Return false Note: Default to boundary
    Return true

Process called "determine_grapheme_cluster_type" that takes codepoints as List[Integer] returns GraphemeClusterType:
    Note: Determine type of grapheme cluster
    If length of codepoints is equal to 1:
    Return BasicCluster Let has_emoji be false
    Let has_modifier be false
    Let has_zwj be false For each codepoint in codepoints:
    If is_emoji with codepoint as codepoint:
    Set has_emoji to true
    If codepoint is equal to 127995 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 127995 and codepoint is less than or equal to 127999:
    Set has_modifier to true
    If codepoint is equal to 8205: Note: Zero Width Joiner
    Set has_zwj to true If has_emoji and has_modifier:
    Return ModifierSequence
    Otherwise if has_emoji and has_zwj:
    Return ZeroWidthJoinerSequence
    Otherwise if has_emoji:
    Return EmojiSequence
    Otherwise:
    Return BasicCluster

Note: Unicode String Comparison and Collation
Process called "unicode_compare" that takes text1 as String and text2 as String and locale as String returns CollationResult:
    Note: Compare Unicode strings with locale-aware collation
    Let normalized1 be normalize_unicode with text as text1 and form as NFC
    Let normalized2 be normalize_unicode with text as text2 and form as NFC Let primary_result be compare_primary_level with text1 as normalized1.normalized_text and text2 as normalized2.normalized_text
    Let secondary_result be 0
    Let tertiary_result be 0 If primary_result is equal to 0:
    Set secondary_result to compare_secondary_level with text1 as normalized1.normalized_text and text2 as normalized2.normalized_text
    If secondary_result is equal to 0:
    Set tertiary_result to compare_tertiary_level with text1 as normalized1.normalized_text and text2 as normalized2.normalized_text Let final_result be if primary_result is not equal to 0 then primary_result else if secondary_result is not equal to 0 then secondary_result else tertiary_result Return CollationResult with:
    comparison_result as final_result
    primary_difference as primary_result
    secondary_difference as secondary_result
    tertiary_difference as tertiary_result
    identical as final_result is equal to 0
    locale as locale
    metadata as dictionary containing "comparison_method" as "unicode_collation"

Process called "compare_primary_level" that takes text1 as String and text2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Compare at primary level (base characters)
    Let codepoints1 be extract_primary_weights with text as text1
    Let codepoints2 be extract_primary_weights with text as text2 Let min_length be if length of codepoints1 is less than length of codepoints2 then length of codepoints1 else length of codepoints2 For i from 0 to (min_length - 1):
    If codepoints1[i] is less than codepoints2[i]:
    Return -1
    Otherwise if codepoints1[i] is greater than codepoints2[i]:
    Return 1 If length of codepoints1 is less than length of codepoints2:
    Return -1
    Otherwise if length of codepoints1 is greater than length of codepoints2:
    Return 1
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "extract_primary_weights" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Extract primary collation weights (ignore case, accents)
    Let result be list containing
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    If not is_combining_mark with codepoint as codepoint:
    Let base_char be get_base_character with codepoint as codepoint
    Add base_char to result Return result

Process called "get_base_character" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get base character without case or accent variations
    Let decomposed be canonical_decomposition with codepoint as codepoint
    If length of decomposed is greater than 0:
    Let base be decomposed[0]
    Return to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as base
    Otherwise:
    Return to_lowercase_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint

Note: Encoding Conversion and Utilities
Process called "string_to_codepoints" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert UTF-8 string to Unicode codepoints
    Let codepoints be list containing
    Let bytes be Format.string_to_bytes with s as text
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of bytes:
    Let byte1 be bytes[i] If byte1 is less than 128:
    Note: Single-byte ASCII
    Add byte1 to codepoints
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 192 and byte1 is less than or equal to 223:
    Note: Two-byte sequence
    If i + 1 is less than length of bytes:
    Let byte2 be bytes[i + 1]
    Let codepoint be ((byte1 and 31) << 6) or (byte2 and 63)
    Add codepoint to codepoints
    Set i to i + 2
    Otherwise:
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 224 and byte1 is less than or equal to 239:
    Note: Three-byte sequence
    If i + 2 is less than length of bytes:
    Let byte2 be bytes[i + 1]
    Let byte3 be bytes[i + 2]
    Let codepoint be ((byte1 and 15) << 12) or ((byte2 and 63) << 6) or (byte3 and 63)
    Add codepoint to codepoints
    Set i to i + 3
    Otherwise:
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 240 and byte1 is less than or equal to 247:
    Note: Four-byte sequence
    If i + 3 is less than length of bytes:
    Let byte2 be bytes[i + 1]
    Let byte3 be bytes[i + 2]
    Let byte4 be bytes[i + 3]
    Let codepoint be ((byte1 and 7) << 18) or ((byte2 and 63) << 12) or ((byte3 and 63) << 6) or (byte4 and 63)
    Add codepoint to codepoints
    Set i to i + 4
    Otherwise:
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise:
    Note: Invalid byte, skip
    Set i to i + 1 Return codepoints

Process called "codepoints_to_string" that takes codepoints as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Convert Unicode codepoints to UTF-8 string
    Let result be ""
    For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Set result to result codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as codepoint Return result

Process called "codepoint_to_utf8" that takes codepoint as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert single codepoint to UTF-8 bytes
    If codepoint is less than 128:
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with code as codepoint
    Otherwise if codepoint is less than 2048:
    Let byte1 be 192 or (codepoint >> 6)
    Let byte2 be 128 or (codepoint and 63)
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte1 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte2
    Otherwise if codepoint is less than 65536:
    Let byte1 be 224 or (codepoint >> 12)
    Let byte2 be 128 or ((codepoint >> 6) and 63)
    Let byte3 be 128 or (codepoint and 63)
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte1 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte2 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte3
    Otherwise if codepoint is less than 1114112:
    Let byte1 be 240 or (codepoint >> 18)
    Let byte2 be 128 or ((codepoint >> 12) and 63)
    Let byte3 be 128 or ((codepoint >> 6) and 63)
    Let byte4 be 128 or (codepoint and 63)
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte1 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte2 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte3 Format.character_from_ascii with code as byte4
    Otherwise:
    Return ""

Process called "codepoint_to_utf16" that takes codepoint as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert codepoint to UTF-16 code units
    If codepoint is less than 65536:
    Return list containing codepoint
    Otherwise:
    Let adjusted be codepoint - 65536
    Let high_surrogate be 55296 + (adjusted >> 10)
    Let low_surrogate be 56320 + (adjusted and 1023)
    Return list containing high_surrogate, low_surrogate

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "lookup_character_info" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Look up character information (simplified implementation)
    Return dictionary containing:
    "name" as "UNKNOWN",
    "combining_class" as 0,
    "numeric_value" as None

Process called "find_unicode_block" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeBlock:
    Note: Find Unicode block containing codepoint
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 0 and codepoint is less than or equal to 127:
    Return UnicodeBlock with:
    name as "Basic Latin"
    start_codepoint as 0
    end_codepoint as 127
    script as Latin
    description as "ASCII characters"
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 128 and codepoint is less than or equal to 255:
    Return UnicodeBlock with:
    name as "Latin-1 Supplement"
    start_codepoint as 128
    end_codepoint as 255
    script as Latin
    description as "Latin-1 supplement"
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Otherwise:
    Return UnicodeBlock with:
    name as "Unknown"
    start_codepoint as codepoint
    end_codepoint as codepoint
    script as Unknown
    description as "Unknown block"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "has_numeric_value" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character has numeric value
    Return codepoint is greater than or equal to 48 and codepoint is less than or equal to 57 or codepoint is greater than or equal to 8304 and codepoint is less than or equal to 8313

Process called "has_text_presentation" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character has default text presentation
    Return not is_emoji with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "has_locale_specific_casing" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character has locale-specific case rules
    Return false Note: Simplified

Process called "is_base_character" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is a base character (not combining)
    Return not is_combining_mark with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "is_combining_mark" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is combining mark
    Let category be classify_character_category with codepoint as codepoint
    Match category:
    When MarkNonspacing:
    Return true
    When MarkSpacingCombining:
    Return true
    When MarkEnclosing:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_word_boundary" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character represents word boundary
    Return is_whitespace with codepoint as codepoint or codepoint is equal to 46 or codepoint is equal to 33 or codepoint is equal to 63

Process called "extract_combining_classes" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Extract combining classes from text
    Let classes be list containing
    Let codepoints be string_to_codepoints with text as text For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Add get_combining_class with codepoint as codepoint to classes Return classes

Process called "get_combining_class" that takes codepoint as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get combining class for character (simplified)
    If codepoint is greater than or equal to 768 and codepoint is less than or equal to 879:
    Return 230 Note: Above marks
    Otherwise if codepoint is greater than or equal to 1155 and codepoint is less than or equal to 1161:
    Return 232 Note: Hebrew points
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "sort_combining_marks" that takes marks as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Sort combining marks by combining class
    Note: Simplified bubble sort implementation
    Let result be marks
    Let n be length of result For i from 0 to (n - 2):
    For j from 0 to (n - i - 2):
    Let class1 be get_combining_class with codepoint as result[j]
    Let class2 be get_combining_class with codepoint as result[j + 1] If class1 is greater than class2 and class1 is greater than 0 and class2 is greater than 0:
    Let temp be result[j]
    Set result at index j to result[j + 1]
    Set result at index (j + 1) to temp Return result

Process called "extract_cluster_properties" that takes codepoints as List[Integer] returns List[UnicodeProperty]:
    Note: Extract properties for grapheme cluster
    Let all_properties be list containing For each codepoint in codepoints:
    Let char_properties be extract_character_properties with codepoint as codepoint
    For each property in char_properties:
    If not contains_property with properties as all_properties and property as property:
    Add property to all_properties Return all_properties

Process called "contains_property" that takes properties as List[UnicodeProperty] and property as UnicodeProperty returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if property list contains specific property
    For each existing_property in properties:
    Match existing_property:
    When Alphabetic:
    Match property:
    When Alphabetic:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Continue
    When Numeric:
    Match property:
    When Numeric:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Continue
    When Emoji:
    Match property:
    When Emoji:
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Continue
    Otherwise:
    Continue Return false

Process called "compare_secondary_level" that takes text1 as String and text2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Compare at secondary level (accents, diacritics)
    Return 0 Note: Simplified implementation

Process called "compare_tertiary_level" that takes text1 as String and text2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Compare at tertiary level (case differences)
    If text1 is less than text2:
    Return -1
    Otherwise if text1 is greater than text2:
    Return 1
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp - would delegate to system in production
    Return 0.0

Note: Public API Functions
Process called "character_info" that takes codepoint as Integer returns UnicodeCharacter:
    Return get_unicode_character with codepoint as codepoint

Process called "normalize" that takes text as String and form as String returns String:
    Let norm_form be match form:
    When "NFC":
    NFC
    When "NFD":
    NFD
    When "NFKC":
    NFKC
    When "NFKD":
    NFKD
    Otherwise:
    NFC Let result be normalize_unicode with text as text and form as norm_form
    Return result.normalized_text

Process called "lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Return unicode_lowercase with text as text

Process called "uppercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Return unicode_uppercase with text as text

Process called "titlecase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Return unicode_titlecase with text as text

Process called "casefold" that takes text as String returns String:
    Return unicode_casefold with text as text

Process called "grapheme_clusters" that takes text as String returns List[String]:
    Let clusters be split_into_grapheme_clusters with text as text
    Let result be list containing For each cluster in clusters:
    Add cluster.text to result Return result

Process called "compare_strings" that takes text1 as String and text2 as String returns Integer:
    Let result be unicode_compare with text1 as text1 and text2 as text2 and locale as "en"
    Return result.comparison_result

Process called "to_codepoints" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Return string_to_codepoints with text as text

Process called "from_codepoints" that takes codepoints as List[Integer] returns String:
    Return codepoints_to_string with codepoints as codepoints